An Erlang clone of http://snip.heroku.com/

By Seven Du from [Idapted Tech Team](http://www.idapted.com)


It using ETS as a in memory database, you can change into DETS or mnesia for permanent store.

You need mochiweb in place. http://code.google.com/p/mochiweb/

make
./start-dev.sh

and browser localhost:8000 in your browser.

Check ETS in erlang console:

ets:tab2list(urls).


enjoy.
